text.tspan: CONVEYOR AND EQUIPMENT BY A.V.W. EQUIPMENT CO.
CONCRETE FOOTINGS AND STRENGTH TO COMPLY
DO NOT SUBSTITUTE FOR ARCHITECTURAL PLAN.
1. ENTRANCE SLOPE DOWNHILL INTO WASH AT 1-2% GRADE
FOR 20'-0" MIN, THEN FLAT FOR 10'-0" ONTO CONVEYOR.
2. SLOPE EQUAL TO 1'' RISE FOR EVERY 40'-0'' MIN. TO 30'-0"
MAX. RISING FROM TUNNEL'S ENTRANCE TO EXIT.
3. EXIT SLOPE FLAT FOR 6'-0" MIN. SO CAR DOES NOT ROLL
OUT TOO EARLY FROM THE DRYER ,THEN DOWNHILL
SLOPE FOR 4'-0" MIN. AT 1-2% GRADE, SO THE CAR ROLLS
THIS DRAWING AND ITS DESIGNS ARE PROPERTY OF AVW EQUIPMENT CO. & IT IS
NOT TO BE USED OR REPRODUCED WITHOUT THE PERMISSION FROM AVW CO.
